!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

heroic /hɪˈrəʊɪk/

(heroics) 

1. ADJ If you describe a person or their actions as heroic , you admire them because they show extreme bravery. 英勇的 

例： His heroic deeds were celebrated in every corner of India. 他的英勇事迹在印度的每个角落被传颂。 

2. heroically ADV 英勇地 [ADV with v] 

例： He had acted heroically during the liner's evacuation. 他在疏散客轮乘客的过程中表现得很英勇。 

3. ADJ If you describe an action or event as heroic , you admire it because it involves great effort or determination to succeed. 艰苦卓绝的 [表赞许] 

例： The company has made heroic efforts at cost reduction. 该公司在降低成本方面进行了艰苦卓绝的努力。 

4. heroically ADV 艰苦卓绝地 

例： Single parents cope heroically in doing the job of two people. 单身父母做着两个人的工作，非常艰苦也非常有毅力。 

5. ADJ Heroic means being or relating to the hero or heroine of a story. 主人公的 

例： ...the book's central, heroic figure. …书中的中心主角人物。 

6. N-PLURAL Heroics are actions involving bravery, courage, or determination. 英雄壮举 

例： ...the man whose aerial heroics helped save the helicopter pilot. …那个以空中的英雄壮举拯救直升机飞行员的人。 

7. N-PLURAL If you describe someone's actions or plans as heroics , you think that they are foolish or dangerous because they are too difficult or brave for the situation in which they occur. 逞能行为 [口语] 

例： He said his advice was: 'No heroics, stay within the law.' 他说他的意见是：“不要有逞能行为，要依法办事。”

